#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="sn22.82"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn22.82:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 22 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 22 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.82:0.2"
msgid "8. Khajjanīyavagga "
msgstr "8. Itchy "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
#. VAR: 82. Puṇṇamasutta → puṇṇamāsuttaṃ (bj) | puṇṇamā (pts1)
msgctxt "sn22.82:0.3"
msgid "82. Puṇṇamasutta "
msgstr "82. A Full Moon Night "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli3.100, sc1
msgctxt "sn22.82:1.1"
msgid "Ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati pubbārāme migāramātupāsāde mahatā bhikkhusaṃghena saddhiṃ. "
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying near Sāvatthī in the Eastern Monastery, the stilt longhouse of Migāra’s mother, together with a large Saṅgha of mendicants. "

msgctxt "sn22.82:1.2"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena bhagavā tadahuposathe pannarase puṇṇāya puṇṇamāya rattiyā bhikkhusaṃghaparivuto ajjhokāse nisinno hoti. "
msgstr "Now, at that time it was the sabbath—the full moon on the fifteenth day—and the Buddha was sitting surrounded by the Saṅgha of monks. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "sn22.82:2.1"
msgid "Atha kho aññataro bhikkhu uṭṭhāyāsanā ekaṃsaṃ uttarāsaṅgaṃ karitvā yena bhagavā tenañjaliṃ paṇāmetvā bhagavantaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "Then one of the mendicants got up from their seat, arranged their robe over one shoulder, raised their joined palms toward the Buddha, and said: "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. VAR: kiñcideva → kañcideva (?)
msgctxt "sn22.82:2.2"
msgid "“puccheyyāhaṃ, bhante, bhagavantaṃ kiñcideva desaṃ, sace me bhagavā okāsaṃ karoti pañhassa veyyākaraṇāyā”ti? "
msgstr "“Sir, I’d like to ask the Buddha about a certain point, if you’d take the time to answer.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.82:2.3"
msgid "“Tena hi tvaṃ, bhikkhu, sake āsane nisīditvā puccha yadākaṅkhasī”ti. "
msgstr "“Well then, mendicant, take your own seat and ask what you wish.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.82:2.4"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho so bhikkhu bhagavato paṭissutvā sake āsane nisīditvā bhagavantaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "“Yes, sir,” replied that mendicant. He took his seat and said to the Buddha: "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.82:2.5"
msgid "“ime nu kho, bhante, pañcupādānakkhandhā, seyyathidaṃ—"
msgstr "“Sir, are these the five grasping aggregates, that is: "

msgctxt "sn22.82:2.6"
msgid "rūpupādānakkhandho, vedanupādānakkhandho, saññupādānakkhandho, saṅkhārupādānakkhandho, viññāṇupādānakkhandho”ti. "
msgstr "form, feeling, perception, choices, and consciousness?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "sn22.82:3.1"
msgid "“Ime kho, bhikkhu, pañcupādānakkhandhā; "
msgstr "“Yes, they are,” replied the Buddha. "

msgctxt "sn22.82:3.2"
msgid "Seyyathidaṃ—rūpupādānakkhandho … pe … viññāṇupādānakkhandho”ti. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.82:3.3"
msgid "“Sādhu, bhante”ti kho so bhikkhu bhagavato bhāsitaṃ abhinanditvā anumoditvā bhagavantaṃ uttariṃ pañhaṃ apucchi: "
msgstr "Saying “Good, sir”, that mendicant approved and agreed with what the Buddha said. Then he asked another question: "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli3.101, sc4
msgctxt "sn22.82:4.1"
msgid "“Ime kho pana, bhante, pañcupādānakkhandhā kiṃmūlakā”ti? "
msgstr "“But sir, what is the root of these five grasping aggregates?” "

# NOTE: It looks like a sadhu passage has been elided here. Indeed, in the parallel at MN 109, this sadhu passage is omitted, and so are the ones following, while here, only this one is omitted.
#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.82:4.2"
msgid "“Ime kho, bhikkhu, pañcupādānakkhandhā chandamūlakā”ti … pe … "
msgstr "“These five grasping aggregates are rooted in desire.” … "

msgctxt "sn22.82:4.3"
msgid "taññeva nu kho, bhante, upādānaṃ te pañcupādānakkhandhā udāhu aññatra pañcahi upādānakkhandhehi upādānan”ti? "
msgstr "“But sir, is that grasping the exact same thing as the five grasping aggregates? Or is grasping one thing and the five grasping aggregates another?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.82:4.4"
msgid "“Na kho, bhikkhu, taññeva upādānaṃ te pañcupādānakkhandhā nāpi aññatra pañcahi upādānakkhandhehi upādānaṃ, api ca yo tattha chandarāgo taṃ tattha upādānan”ti. "
msgstr "“Neither. Rather, the desire and greed for them is the grasping there.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.82:4.5"
msgid "“Sādhu, bhante”ti kho so bhikkhu … pe … uttariṃ pañhaṃ apucchi: "
msgstr "Saying “Good, sir”, that mendicant asked another question: "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc5
msgctxt "sn22.82:5.1"
msgid "“Siyā pana, bhante, pañcupādānakkhandhesu chandarāgavemattatā”ti? "
msgstr "“But sir, can there be different kinds of desire and greed for the five grasping aggregates?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.82:5.2"
msgid "“Siyā, bhikkhū”ti bhagavā avoca: "
msgstr "“There can,” said the Buddha. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.82:5.3"
msgid "“idha, bhikkhu, ekaccassa evaṃ hoti: "
msgstr "“It’s when someone thinks: "

msgctxt "sn22.82:5.4"
msgid "‘evaṃrūpo siyaṃ anāgatamaddhānaṃ, evaṃvedano siyaṃ anāgatamaddhānaṃ, evaṃsañño siyaṃ anāgatamaddhānaṃ, evaṃsaṅkhāro siyaṃ anāgatamaddhānaṃ, evaṃviññāṇo siyaṃ anāgatamaddhānan’ti. "
msgstr "‘In the future, may I be of such form, such feeling, such perception, such choices, or such consciousness!’ "

# NOTE: MS question mark here is incorrect.
msgctxt "sn22.82:5.5"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, bhikkhu, siyā pañcupādānakkhandhesu chandarāgavemattatā”ti? "
msgstr "That’s how there can be different kinds of desire and greed for the five grasping aggregates.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.82:5.6"
msgid "“Sādhu, bhante”ti kho so bhikkhu … pe … uttariṃ pañhaṃ apucchi: "
msgstr "Saying “Good, sir”, that mendicant asked another question: "

# NOTE: BB’s “in what way” is not quite right here. kittavata means “to what extent” and is used to define or delineate. The question is whether there’s anything outside the khandhas.
#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc6
msgctxt "sn22.82:6.1"
msgid "“Kittāvatā nu kho, bhante, khandhānaṃ khandhādhivacanan”ti? "
msgstr "“Sir, what is the scope of the term ‘aggregates’ as applied to the aggregates?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.82:6.2"
msgid "“Yaṃ kiñci, bhikkhu, rūpaṃ atītānāgatapaccuppannaṃ ajjhattaṃ vā bahiddhā vā oḷārikaṃ vā sukhumaṃ vā hīnaṃ vā paṇītaṃ vā yaṃ dūre santike vā, ayaṃ vuccati rūpakkhandho. "
msgstr "“Any kind of form at all—past, future, or present; internal or external; coarse or fine; inferior or superior; far or near: this is called the aggregate of form. "

msgctxt "sn22.82:6.3"
msgid "Yā kāci vedanā … "
msgstr "Any kind of feeling at all … "

msgctxt "sn22.82:6.4"
msgid "yā kāci saññā … "
msgstr "Any kind of perception at all … "

msgctxt "sn22.82:6.5"
msgid "ye keci saṅkhārā … "
msgstr "Any kind of choices at all … "

msgctxt "sn22.82:6.6"
msgid "yaṃ kiñci viññāṇaṃ atītānāgatapaccuppannaṃ ajjhattaṃ vā bahiddhā vā oḷārikaṃ vā sukhumaṃ vā hīnaṃ vā paṇītaṃ vā yaṃ dūre santike vā, ayaṃ vuccati viññāṇakkhandho. "
msgstr "Any kind of consciousness at all—past, future, or present; internal or external; coarse or fine; inferior or superior; far or near: this is called the aggregate of consciousness. "

msgctxt "sn22.82:6.7"
msgid "Ettāvatā kho, bhikkhu, khandhānaṃ khandhādhivacanan”ti. "
msgstr "That’s the scope of the term ‘aggregates’ as applied to the aggregates.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.82:6.8"
msgid "“Sādhu, bhante”ti kho so bhikkhu … pe … apucchi: "
msgstr "Saying “Good, sir”, that mendicant asked another question: "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli3.102, sc7
msgctxt "sn22.82:7.1"
msgid "“Ko nu kho, bhante, hetu ko paccayo rūpakkhandhassa paññāpanāya; "
msgstr "“What is the cause, sir, what is the reason why the aggregate of form is found? "

msgctxt "sn22.82:7.2"
msgid "ko hetu ko paccayo vedanākkhandhassa paññāpanāya; "
msgstr "What is the cause, what is the reason why the aggregate of feeling … "

msgctxt "sn22.82:7.3"
msgid "ko hetu ko paccayo saññākkhandhassa paññāpanāya; "
msgstr "perception … "

msgctxt "sn22.82:7.4"
msgid "ko hetu ko paccayo saṅkhārakkhandhassa paññāpanāya; "
msgstr "choices … "

msgctxt "sn22.82:7.5"
msgid "ko hetu ko paccayo viññāṇakkhandhassa paññāpanāyā”ti? "
msgstr "consciousness is found?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.82:7.6"
msgid "“Cattāro kho, bhikkhu, mahābhūtā hetu, cattāro mahābhūtā paccayo rūpakkhandhassa paññāpanāya. "
msgstr "“The four primary elements are the reason why the aggregate of form is found. "

msgctxt "sn22.82:7.7"
msgid "Phasso hetu phasso paccayo vedanākkhandhassa paññāpanāya. "
msgstr "Contact is the reason why the aggregates of feeling, "

msgctxt "sn22.82:7.8"
msgid "Phasso hetu phasso paccayo saññākkhandhassa paññāpanāya. "
msgstr "perception, "

msgctxt "sn22.82:7.9"
msgid "Phasso hetu, phasso paccayo saṅkhārakkhandhassa paññāpanāya. "
msgstr "and choices are found. "

msgctxt "sn22.82:7.10"
msgid "Nāmarūpaṃ hetu, nāmarūpaṃ paccayo viññāṇakkhandhassa paññāpanāyā”ti. "
msgstr "Name and form are the reasons why the aggregate of consciousness is found.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.82:7.11"
msgid "“Sādhu, bhante”ti kho so bhikkhu … pe … apucchi: "
msgstr "Saying “Good, sir”, that mendicant asked another question: "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc8
msgctxt "sn22.82:8.1"
msgid "“Kathaṃ nu kho, bhante, sakkāyadiṭṭhi hotī”ti? "
msgstr "“Sir, how does identity view come about?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.82:8.2"
msgid "“Idha, bhikkhu, assutavā puthujjano ariyānaṃ adassāvī ariyadhammassa akovido ariyadhamme avinīto, sappurisānaṃ adassāvī sappurisadhammassa akovido sappurisadhamme avinīto "
msgstr "“It’s because an uneducated ordinary person has not seen the noble ones, and is neither skilled nor trained in the teaching of the noble ones. They’ve not seen good persons, and are neither skilled nor trained in the teaching of the good persons. "

msgctxt "sn22.82:8.3"
msgid "rūpaṃ attato samanupassati, rūpavantaṃ vā attānaṃ; attani vā rūpaṃ, rūpasmiṃ vā attānaṃ; "
msgstr "They regard form as self, self as having form, form in self, or self in form. "

msgctxt "sn22.82:8.4"
msgid "vedanaṃ … "
msgstr "They regard feeling … "

msgctxt "sn22.82:8.5"
msgid "saññaṃ … "
msgstr "perception … "

msgctxt "sn22.82:8.6"
msgid "saṅkhāre … "
msgstr "choices … "

msgctxt "sn22.82:8.7"
msgid "viññāṇaṃ attato samanupassati, viññāṇavantaṃ vā attānaṃ; attani vā viññāṇaṃ, viññāṇasmiṃ vā attānaṃ. "
msgstr "consciousness as self, self as having consciousness, consciousness in self, or self in consciousness. "

msgctxt "sn22.82:8.8"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, bhikkhu, sakkāyadiṭṭhi hotī”ti. "
msgstr "That’s how identity view comes about.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.82:8.9"
msgid "“Sādhu, bhante”ti kho so bhikkhu … pe … apucchi: "
msgstr "Saying “Good, sir”, that mendicant … asked another question: "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc9
msgctxt "sn22.82:9.1"
msgid "“Kathaṃ pana, bhante, sakkāyadiṭṭhi na hotī”ti? "
msgstr "“But sir, how does identity view not come about?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.82:9.2"
msgid "“Idha, bhikkhu, sutavā ariyasāvako ariyānaṃ dassāvī ariyadhammassa kovido ariyadhamme suvinīto, sappurisānaṃ dassāvī sappurisadhammassa kovido sappurisadhamme suvinīto "
msgstr "It’s because an educated noble disciple has seen the noble ones, and is skilled and trained in the teaching of the noble ones. They’ve seen good persons, and are skilled and trained in the teaching of the good persons. "

msgctxt "sn22.82:9.3"
msgid "na rūpaṃ attato samanupassati, na rūpavantaṃ vā attānaṃ; na attani vā rūpaṃ, na rūpasmiṃ vā attānaṃ; "
msgstr "They don’t regard form as self, self as having form, form in self, or self in form. "

msgctxt "sn22.82:9.4"
msgid "na vedanaṃ … "
msgstr "They don’t regard feeling … "

msgctxt "sn22.82:9.5"
msgid "na saññaṃ … "
msgstr "perception … "

msgctxt "sn22.82:9.6"
msgid "na saṅkhāre … "
msgstr "choices … "

msgctxt "sn22.82:9.7"
msgid "na viññāṇaṃ attato samanupassati, na viññāṇavantaṃ vā attānaṃ; na attani vā viññāṇaṃ, na viññāṇasmiṃ vā attānaṃ. "
msgstr "consciousness as self, self as having consciousness, consciousness in self, or self in consciousness. "

msgctxt "sn22.82:9.8"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, bhikkhu, sakkāyadiṭṭhi na hotī”ti. "
msgstr "That’s how identity view does not come about.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.82:9.9"
msgid "“Sādhu, bhante”ti kho so bhikkhu … pe … apucchi: "
msgstr "Saying “Good, sir”, that mendicant … asked another question: "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli3.103, sc10
msgctxt "sn22.82:10.1"
msgid "“Ko nu kho, bhante, rūpassa assādo, ko ādīnavo, kiṃ nissaraṇaṃ; "
msgstr "“Sir, what’s the gratification, the drawback, and the escape when it comes to form, "

msgctxt "sn22.82:10.2"
msgid "ko vedanāya … "
msgstr "feeling, "

msgctxt "sn22.82:10.3"
msgid "ko saññāya … "
msgstr "perception, "

msgctxt "sn22.82:10.4"
msgid "ko saṅkhārānaṃ … "
msgstr "choices, "

msgctxt "sn22.82:10.5"
msgid "ko viññāṇassa assādo, ko ādīnavo, kiṃ nissaraṇan”ti? "
msgstr "and consciousness?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.82:10.6"
msgid "“Yaṃ kho, bhikkhu, rūpaṃ paṭicca uppajjati sukhaṃ somanassaṃ—ayaṃ rūpassa assādo. "
msgstr "“The pleasure and happiness that arise from form: this is its gratification. "

msgctxt "sn22.82:10.7"
msgid "Yaṃ rūpaṃ aniccaṃ dukkhaṃ vipariṇāmadhammaṃ—ayaṃ rūpassa ādīnavo. "
msgstr "That form is impermanent, suffering, and perishable: this is its drawback. "

msgctxt "sn22.82:10.8"
msgid "Yo rūpasmiṃ chandarāgavinayo chandarāgappahānaṃ—idaṃ rūpassa nissaraṇaṃ. "
msgstr "Removing and giving up desire and greed for form: this is its escape. "

msgctxt "sn22.82:10.9"
msgid "Yaṃ vedanaṃ paṭicca … "
msgstr "The pleasure and happiness that arise from feeling … "

msgctxt "sn22.82:10.10"
msgid "yaṃ saññaṃ paṭicca … "
msgstr "perception … "

msgctxt "sn22.82:10.11"
msgid "ye saṅkhāre paṭicca … "
msgstr "choices … "

msgctxt "sn22.82:10.12"
msgid "yaṃ viññāṇaṃ paṭicca uppajjati sukhaṃ somanassaṃ—ayaṃ viññāṇassa assādo. "
msgstr "consciousness: this is its gratification. "

msgctxt "sn22.82:10.13"
msgid "Yaṃ viññāṇaṃ aniccaṃ dukkhaṃ vipariṇāmadhammaṃ—ayaṃ viññāṇassa ādīnavo. "
msgstr "That consciousness is impermanent, suffering, and perishable: this is its drawback. "

msgctxt "sn22.82:10.14"
msgid "Yo viññāṇasmiṃ chandarāgavinayo chandarāgappahānaṃ—idaṃ viññāṇassa nissaraṇan”ti. "
msgstr "Removing and giving up desire and greed for consciousness: this is its escape.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.82:10.15"
msgid "“Sādhu, bhante”ti kho so bhikkhu bhagavato bhāsitaṃ abhinanditvā anumoditvā bhagavantaṃ uttariṃ pañhaṃ apucchi: "
msgstr "Saying “Good, sir”, that mendicant approved and agreed with what the Buddha said. Then he asked another question: "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc11
msgctxt "sn22.82:11.1"
msgid "“Kathaṃ nu kho, bhante, jānato, kathaṃ passato imasmiñca saviññāṇake kāye bahiddhā ca sabbanimittesu ahaṅkāramamaṅkāramānānusayā na hontī”ti? "
msgstr "“Sir, how does one know and see so that there’s no ego, possessiveness, or underlying tendency to conceit for this conscious body and all external stimuli?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.82:11.2"
msgid "“Yaṃ kiñci, bhikkhu, rūpaṃ atītānāgatapaccuppannaṃ ajjhattaṃ vā bahiddhā vā oḷārikaṃ vā sukhumaṃ vā hīnaṃ vā paṇītaṃ vā yaṃ dūre santike vā, sabbaṃ rūpaṃ: ‘netaṃ mama, nesohamasmi, na meso attā’ti evametaṃ yathābhūtaṃ sammappaññāya passati. "
msgstr "“One truly sees any kind of form at all—past, future, or present; internal or external; coarse or fine; inferior or superior; far or near: *all* form—with right understanding: ‘This is not mine, I am not this, this is not my self.’ "

msgctxt "sn22.82:11.3"
msgid "Yā kāci vedanā … "
msgstr "They truly see any kind of feeling … "

msgctxt "sn22.82:11.4"
msgid "yā kāci saññā … "
msgstr "perception … "

msgctxt "sn22.82:11.5"
msgid "ye keci saṅkhārā … "
msgstr "choices … "

msgctxt "sn22.82:11.6"
msgid "yaṃ kiñci viññāṇaṃ atītānāgatapaccuppannaṃ ajjhattaṃ vā bahiddhā vā oḷārikaṃ vā sukhumaṃ vā hīnaṃ vā paṇītaṃ vā yaṃ dūre santike vā, sabbaṃ viññāṇaṃ: ‘netaṃ mama, nesohamasmi, na meso attā’ti evametaṃ yathābhūtaṃ sammappaññāya passati. "
msgstr "consciousness at all—past, future, or present; internal or external; coarse or fine; inferior or superior; far or near, *all* consciousness—with right understanding: ‘This is not mine, I am not this, this is not my self.’ "

msgctxt "sn22.82:11.7"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, bhikkhu, jānato evaṃ passato imasmiñca saviññāṇake kāye bahiddhā ca sabbanimittesu ahaṅkāramamaṅkāramānānusayā na hontī”ti. "
msgstr "That’s how to know and see so that there’s no ego, possessiveness, or underlying tendency to conceit for this conscious body and all external stimuli.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc12
msgctxt "sn22.82:12.1"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena aññatarassa bhikkhuno evaṃ cetaso parivitakko udapādi: "
msgstr "Now at that time one of the mendicants had the thought: "

# NOTE: Here and in the parallel passage at MN 108, BB omits the bho, without comment. Thanissaro does likewise. However it appears in both cases, without variants. In fact the idiom iti kira is invariably followed by a vocative, so it can’t be a mistake. Horner translates it in MN 108, with the note: “This looks like a case where a monk, in thought, applies bho to himself. Or else he is thinking (as translated at K.S. iii. 88) “so then you say.” ”
#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.82:12.2"
msgid "“iti kira bho rūpaṃ anattā, vedanā … saññā … saṅkhārā … viññāṇaṃ anattā; "
msgstr "“So it seems, good sir, that form, feeling, perception, choices, and consciousness are not-self. "

#. VAR: kathamattānaṃ → kammattānaṃ (s1-3, km, mr) | katamattānaṃ (pts1)
msgctxt "sn22.82:12.3"
msgid "anattakatāni kammāni kathamattānaṃ phusissantī”ti. "
msgstr "Then what self will the deeds done by not-self affect?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.82:12.4"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā tassa bhikkhuno cetasā ceto parivitakkamaññāya bhikkhū āmantesi: "
msgstr "Then the Buddha, knowing what that monk was thinking, addressed the mendicants: "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli3.104, sc13
msgctxt "sn22.82:13.1"
msgid "“Ṭhānaṃ kho panetaṃ, bhikkhave, vijjati yaṃ idhekacco moghapuriso avidvā avijjāgato taṇhādhipateyyena cetasā satthusāsanaṃ atidhāvitabbaṃ maññeyya. "
msgstr "“It’s possible that some foolish person here—unknowing and ignorant, their mind dominated by craving—thinks they can overstep the teacher’s instructions. They think: "

msgctxt "sn22.82:13.2"
msgid "‘Iti kira, bho, rūpaṃ anattā, vedanā … saññā … saṅkhārā … viññāṇaṃ anattā. "
msgstr "‘So it seems, good sir, that form, feeling, perception, choices, and consciousness are not-self. "

msgctxt "sn22.82:13.3"
msgid "Anattakatāni kammāni kathamattānaṃ phusissantī’ti? "
msgstr "Then what self will the deeds done by not-self affect?’ "

# NOTE: Once again, BB translates tatra tatra as “here and there”, though it is barely intelligible. Clearly here, as usual, a strongly distributive sense is required.
msgctxt "sn22.82:13.4"
msgid "Paṭipucchāvinītā kho me tumhe, bhikkhave, tatra tatra tesu tesu dhammesu. "
msgstr "Now, mendicants, you have been educated by me in questioning with regards to all these things in all such cases. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc14
msgctxt "sn22.82:14.1"
msgid "Taṃ kiṃ maññatha, bhikkhave, "
msgstr "What do you think, mendicants? "

msgctxt "sn22.82:14.2"
msgid "rūpaṃ niccaṃ vā aniccaṃ vā”ti? "
msgstr "Is form permanent or impermanent?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.82:14.3"
msgid "“Aniccaṃ, bhante”. "
msgstr "“Impermanent, sir.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.82:14.4"
msgid "“Vedanā … "
msgstr "“Is feeling … "

msgctxt "sn22.82:14.5"
msgid "saññā … "
msgstr "perception … "

msgctxt "sn22.82:14.6"
msgid "saṅkhārā … "
msgstr "choices … "

msgctxt "sn22.82:14.7"
msgid "viññāṇaṃ niccaṃ vā aniccaṃ vā”ti? "
msgstr "consciousness permanent or impermanent?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.82:14.8"
msgid "“Aniccaṃ, bhante”. "
msgstr "“Impermanent, sir.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.82:14.9"
msgid "“Yaṃ panāniccaṃ dukkhaṃ vā taṃ sukhaṃ vā”ti? "
msgstr "“But if it’s impermanent, is it suffering or happiness?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.82:14.10"
msgid "“Dukkhaṃ, bhante”. "
msgstr "“Suffering, sir.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.82:14.11"
msgid "“Yaṃ panāniccaṃ dukkhaṃ vipariṇāmadhammaṃ, kallaṃ nu taṃ samanupassituṃ: "
msgstr "“But if it’s impermanent, suffering, and perishable, is it fit to be regarded thus: "

msgctxt "sn22.82:14.12"
msgid "‘etaṃ mama, esohamasmi, eso me attā’”ti? "
msgstr "‘This is mine, I am this, this is my self’?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.82:14.13"
msgid "“No hetaṃ, bhante”. "
msgstr "“No, sir.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.82:14.14"
msgid "Tasmātiha … pe … "
msgstr "“So you should truly see … "

msgctxt "sn22.82:14.15"
msgid "evaṃ passaṃ … pe … "
msgstr "Seeing this … "

msgctxt "sn22.82:14.16"
msgid "nāparaṃ itthattāyāti pajānātī”ti. "
msgstr "They understand: ‘… there is no return to any state of existence.’” "

# NOTE: This is very unusual, a sutta-uddana.
#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. REF: sc15
msgctxt "sn22.82:15.1"
msgid "“Dve khandhā taññeva siyaṃ, "
msgstr "“Two on the aggregates; exactly the same; and can there be; "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn22.82:15.2"
msgid "adhivacanañca hetunā; "
msgstr "on the term; and on the cause; "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn22.82:15.3"
msgid "Sakkāyena duve vuttā, "
msgstr "two questions on identity; "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn22.82:15.4"
msgid "assādaviññāṇakena ca; "
msgstr "gratification; and that with consciousness: "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn22.82:15.5"
msgid "Ete dasavidhā vuttā, "
msgstr "these are the ten questions "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn22.82:15.6"
msgid "hoti bhikkhu pucchāyā”ti. "
msgstr "the mendicant came to ask.” "

#. HTML: </p></blockquote><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn22.82:15.7"
msgid "Dasamaṃ. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn22.82:15.8"
msgid "Khajjanīyavaggo tatiyo. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="uddanagatha"><p>
#. REF: sc16
msgctxt "sn22.82:16.1"
msgid "Assādo dve samudayā, "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn22.82:16.2"
msgid "arahantehi apare dve; "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn22.82:16.3"
msgid "Sīho khajjanī piṇḍolyaṃ, "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn22.82:16.4"
msgid "pālileyyena puṇṇamāti. "
msgstr ""

#. HTML: </p></blockquote></article></section></body></html>
